casebody.data:
EMMA J. CROUCH v. CHICAGO GREAT WESTERN RAILROAD COMPANY.1

Same ease as that on page 447, supra.

No. 26,687. On February 10, 1928, the following opinion was filed:

Reported in 217 N. W.-.

 PER CURIAM.

Action for personal injuries. There was a verdict for the plaintiff. The defendant appeals from the judgment.

The case was here before and is reported as Crouch v. Chicago Great Western Railroad Company; supra, p. 447. The questions involved on this appeal are the same as those involved upon the former one, and for the reasons there given the judgment is affirmed.
